message.content:
An ocarina is a musical instrument that belongs to the family of wind instruments. 
It is typically made of ceramic, clay, or other similar materials. 
The ocarina usually has a roundish or oval shape, with a small mouthpiece, finger holes, and a sound hole. 
They come in various sizes, colors, and textures, and can weigh anywhere from a few ounces to a pound. 
The ocarina is typically held and played with two hands. 
This instrument is often used to play folk or traditional music, as well as in video game soundtracks. 
Ocarinas can be found extensively throughout the world, and their history dates back thousands of years.
